Halve, peel and finely chop the @onion{1} into ½cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a garlic press). Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}, halve lengthways then chop into 1cm cubes. Pick the @coriander{1/2}(leaves picked from stalks and finely chopped) from their stalks and finely chop both, but keep them separate. Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, remove the seeds and finely chop.

Put a large #saucepan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}. Add the @onion{} and cook until softened, ~{5%minutes}. Add the @fennel{1/2%tsp}, @ground coriander{1.5%tsp}, @ground cumin{1.5%tsp}, @red chilli{} (use less if you don't like spice!) and half the @ground turmeric{3/4%tsp}. Cook together for ~{1%minute}. Add the @basmati rice{150%g} to your pan along with the @courgette{} and the @coriander stalks{}(from the other half of the coriander). Stir so the rice is nicely coated in the spices.

Pour in the @water{300%ml}. Add the @chicken stock pot{1} and @cinnamon stick{1}. Stir to dissolve the stock pot and bring to a boil. Turn the heat to medium low, pop on a #lid{} and leave to cook for ~{10%minutes} then remove the #pan{} from the heat and leave to rest with the lid on for another ~{10%minutes}. The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

In a #mixing bowl{} combine half the @coriander leaves{1/2} with the remaining @ground turmeric{1/4%tsp} and the @olive oil{}. Add the @chicken thigh{4} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Mix well until the chicken is evenly coated.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil) and add the @desiccated coconut{25%g}. Stir and toast until golden, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from your pan and set aside.

Wipe out the pan with some #kitchen paper{} and pop it back on medium-high heat. Once hot, lay in the chicken, skin-side down. Cook for ~{4-5%minutes}. Turn and cook for another ~{8%minutes}, turning every 3 mins until browned and cooked through. > The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Once cooked, remove the chicken to a #board{} to rest for ~{2%minutes}.

Remove the cinnamon stick from the rice and fluff it up with a #fork{}. Stir through half the remaining coriander leaves and half the toasted coconut. Stir the remaining coconut into the @Greek style natural yoghurt{1}. Cut the chicken into 1cm wide slices. Spoon the rice into #bowls{} and pop the chicken on top. Finish with a dollop of coconut yoghurt and the rest of the coriander leaves. Enjoy!